	<sectionContent_html>&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;In order to protect the few assets you may have as a young couple, it's recommended that you consider increasing your life cover to provide for the costs of your funeral and any other costs directly relating to your death. This will ensure that your surviving partner won&amp;rsquo;t need to sell off any assets to fund those costs. Much of the planning that you do around your life insurance policy value and your estate planning will revolve around the marriage regime you&amp;rsquo;re married under. That&amp;rsquo;s the reason why you need to understand what the marriage regime options are and carefully consider which one you and your partner will opt for.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 class="text--md" style="color: var(--color-text-heading); margin-bottom: var(--space-sm); line-height: var(--heading-line-height); font-weight: 500; font-size: var(--text-md); font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;Conclusion&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;Life insurance, disability, illness and dread disease cover are all forms of insurance that we least enjoy talking about. Consequently, we don&amp;rsquo;t talk about them and then when these disasters happen, they take us by surprise, leaving lasting financial damage. We want to make sure that you are prepared with insurance cover that will be there for you if the worst happens.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;In today&amp;rsquo;s blog post, we&amp;rsquo;ve given you a brief look at the world of life and disability cover and how these policies can help you and your partner survive financially when the worst happens. We learned that we need to start by taking stock of your current financial obligations and the contribution that each partner makes to meeting those obligations. Then, we explained that you may want to opt for additional cover like dread disease and illness cover to manage any shortfall between your life insurance and your new ongoing expenses. Third, we stressed the importance of choosing cover that allows you to continue living your life the way you need to so that you can make your insurance payments as long as is required. Finally, we had a quick look at marriage and how it can impact your insurance planning.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;Phew, that was a lot to take in! If you have any questions (of course you do!) then schedule a call with one of our relationship consultants to discuss your finances and how you can become money smart.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9; text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;button class="btn btn--primary get_started_home_navbar_button" style="font-family: inherit; font-size: var(--btn-font-size); line-height: 1; margin: 0px; overflow: visible; appearance: button; display: inline-flex; position: relative; white-space: nowrap; justify-content: center; padding: var(--space-xs) var(--space-sm); border-radius: var(--btn-radius); border-color: transparent; transition: all 0.2s ease 0s; cursor: pointer; background-color: #e01f26; min-width: 196px; color: #ffffff !important;" role="button" data-tf-slider="Sgz7HGMv" data-tf-width="550" data-tf-hidden="utm_source=CTA,utm_medium=website,utm_campaign=velocityclub_site,utm_term=,utm_content=" data-tf-loaded="true"&gt;Book a session&lt;/button&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</sectionContent_html>
